headline: AbbVie’s US$100b Drug Pricing Pact Reshapes Growth And Policy Outlook
summary: AbbVie (NYSE:ABBV) announced a multi year voluntary agreement with the U.S. government to support access and affordability of medicines. The company committed $100b to U.S. based research and development and capital investments, alongside expanded manufacturing and direct to patient delivery. The agreement is tied to a broader federal policy initiative on drug pricing with potential implications for industry wide pricing and access models. AbbVie enters this agreement with the U.S...
